<section data-depth="1" id="fs-id1165447857255" class="free-response"><h3 data-type="title">Critical Thinking Questions</h3>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165447772028">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165447768185"><p id="fs-id1165447768186">Which vessels and what part of the nephron are involved in countercurrent multiplication?</p></div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1165447768190" data-label="">
<p id="fs-id1165447768193">The vasa recta and loop of Henle are involved in countercurrent multiplication.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1165447860710">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1165447860713"><p id="fs-id1165447860714">Give the approximate osmolarity of fluid in the proximal convoluted tubule, deepest part of the loop of Henle, distal convoluted tubule, and the collecting ducts.</p></div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1165447816277" data-label="">
<p id="fs-id1165447816280">The approximate osmolarities are: CT = 300; deepest loop = 1200; DCT = 100; and collecting ducts = 100&#8211;1200.</p>
</div>
